<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!--
  Permit cleartext (plain HTTP) so the app can reach a self-hosted Plex Media
  Server at its LAN address (issue #171).

  WHY: Plex's secure local URL is a `*.plex.direct` hostname that resolves to a
  PRIVATE LAN IP via PUBLIC DNS. Routers with DNS-rebind protection (e.g. AVM
  FritzBox, on by default) refuse to return a private-IP answer for a public
  lookup, so that URL fails with "Unable to resolve host ….plex.direct". The app
  therefore connects to the server's raw-IP local connection (http://<ip>:32400),
  which is plaintext and needs this allowance — targetSdk 34+ blocks cleartext by
  default.

  SCOPE: Android's network-security-config cannot express private-IP CIDR ranges,
  and the PMS LAN IP is DHCP-assigned, so a base-config is used. This does NOT
  weaken the app's other traffic: Firebase, TMDB, and plex.tv are all HTTPS and
  are never downgraded — the only cleartext destination in practice is the
  user's own LAN Plex server.
-->
<network-security-config>
    <base-config cleartextTrafficPermitted="true" />
</network-security-config>
